TopicTitle: 1st touchdown on Eelloo in 0.20 for me

Articles.Content:
I have waited so long to do this and finally:

I set foot on Eelloo and marked it with my flag. I'm so proud of myself so I needed to share my accomplishment.

Here you can see Marbus Kerman posing:

Congrats! You landed on the furthest reach of Kerbin.

Which happens to be a large, dirty snowball.

For being so small, that lander is really heavy with all those LV-Ns.

I didn't know exactly how much D/V I would need. So I build the biggest Rocket I could with 6 LV-Ns total.

As you see on the name of the craft I got a little frustrated in the building process. *cough*

Edited May 28, 2013 by blspblackdeath

Well done.

That launch vehicle gives me the fear!

I have only sent probes that far, and in 0.19.1 at that. So congratulations on that accomplishment.

Now...are you bringing him back to Kerbin?

He has almost full tanks. So he is heading back by the next tranfer window.

The craftfile if someone is interested:

https://www.dropbox.com/s/d903ubgr2yerzsd/Motherf___ing%20Eelloo%20Mk%20II.craft

Should all be stock parts.
